Name: SMF30InstFlgs1MRS
Description: Instruction Counter related flags. If a bit in this byte is on in the subtype 2/3 record, it is on in the subtype 4 record. Similarly, this holds between subtype 4 and subtype 5 records.

Name: SMF30_Inst_CP_Task
Description: The number of instructions executed while running on a standard processor as a task when it is not eligible for an offload processor and it is not associated with an enclave.

Name: SMF30_Inst_CP_NonPreemptSRB
Description: The number of instructions executed while running on a standard processor as a non-preemptable SRB.

Name: SMF30_Inst_CP_PreemptSRB
Description: The number of instructions executed while running on a standard processor as a preemptable or client SRB when it is not associated with an enclave.

Name: SMF30_Inst_Offload
Description: The number of instructions executed while running on an offload processor when not associated with an enclave.

Name: SMF30_Inst_OffloadOnCP
Description: The number of instructions executed while running on a standard processor as eligible for an offload processor while not associated with an enclave.

Name: SMF30_Inst_CP_Enclave
Description: The number of instructions executed while running on a standard processor as not eligible for an offload processor for an independent enclave.

Name: SMF30_Inst_Offload_Enclave
Description: The number of instructions executed while running on an offload processor for an independent enclave.

Name: SMF30_Inst_OffloadOnCP_Enclave
Description: The number of instructions executed while running on a standard processor as eligible for an offload processor for an independent enclave.

Name: SMF30_Inst_CP_DepEnc
Description: The number of instructions executed while running on a standard processor as not eligible for an offload processor for a dependent enclave.

Name: SMF30_Inst_Offload_DepEnc
Description: The number of instructions executed while running on an offload processor for a dependent enclave.

Name: SMF30_Inst_OffloadOnCP_DepEnc
Description: The number of instructions executed while running on a standard processor as eligible for an offload processor for a dependent enclave.
